A soft yet stern woman, Artemis' gaze sums her personality up aptly. Her eyes are peaceful, oceanic blue that shine in the light like tropical waters in the summer sun. Her gaze, however, is piercing and judgemental. Harsh and unforgiving. You feel yourself being examined both externally and internally just by catching her gaze.

Thie scar-riddled old human looks to be in the twilight of his middle years, grey and wrinkled but still quite capable. That is, if he tried. Instead he sits about, smoking and growling. Once, his man was the model Admiral in the Republic Navy. Now, he almost always has a flask of alcohol in his coat and looks to have not washed in quite some time.

This oddly cheery Arkanian man carries himself with the calm confidence of an elder, despite looking hardly halfway into his twenties. He regards you with a friendly and serene smile, seemingly unafraid of the unknowns of the world around him. His nose is pointed but small, his jawline pronounced and with cheekbones just as defined. His eyes are normal for an Arkanian; pure white without pupils.

He wears loose-fitting tunics that are either covering a suit of fur armour or simply his bare chest, with tight pants that are met at the top of his calves by leather boots. On his back and belt are a great many trinkets, vials and scrolls, suggesting an origin of adventure and life on the road. Wrapped around his neck at all times would be a snugly fit leather necklace with a silver pendant on it near his throat, in the shape of a pine tree.
